Tea Villa Cafe in Kandivali has a far more vibrant setup as against the more traditional one.
F&B perspective, stays true to it's standards & delivers quality!
One of the very few places open late night, this outlet turned out to be out late night grub spot.

The new menu and new dishes added to the tea villa menu are really good. Not just that but the summer menu is good too. They come up with these seasonal menus which is excellent.

Tried a couple of dishes here from the summer and the new menu. Loved a few.

Do try the Sichuan Sliders. They were delicious. Crisp patty, spicy sauce.. one lipsmacking slider. The noodle bhel salad accompanied was to die for.

The potato wedges were crisp and delicious. Loved the seasoning.

Crispy cracker mousse from the summer menu.. creamy smooth Mushroom mousse and spicy guacamole topped over a crisp cracker. It was quite good. A balance of textures..  creamy, spicy, crispy and smooth.

Power protein salad from the summer menu.. this salad was delicious. Loved it. Chickpeas, Arugula, almonds, edamame and quinoa with a super delicious dressing.

Red and black combo from summer menu.. Manipur edamame black rice served with a coconut based chickpeas and Vegetable curry. This dish was delicious and healthy.

Sweet curd with mango .. from the summer menu.. a delicious yougurt with mango sorbet..I quite liked this one.

Chocolate Churros... Oh so good. Loved them. Do try!
Big fat churros drizzled with dark, milk and white chocolate and served with more Chocolate sauce.

Paneer Makhani sizzler... This one was decent..but my least favourite since I'm not a Makhani fan. The pulav was delicious. The paneer was melt in the mouth soft.. the gravy was a little sweet for my liking.

Cottage cheese rolls with Crunchy oats... These could have been better. The cottage cheese and the sauce within was delicious but the outer skin can be worked on.

Kashmiri kawah/twings and berries.. both the teas were good.

Overall a good experience.

A fine dining resturant in Kandivali food hub-Thakur village. Aavakay-The Andhra Kitchen as the name implies specializes for authentic Andhra cuisine. It is one of its kind place for fine dining.

Location/Ambiance: It is conveniently located considering crowd from Inox multiplex and foodies of Thakur village. Ambience is classy with luxurious confortable sofas. It is divided into compartments separated by pillars. Soothing background music adds to the experience.

Menu: They provide 4 different spices and 2 pickles which enhances the dining experience. They also give complimentary fried kurkure. Really crispy and in good portion.

Analysis-
> Mirapakay baji -
Mirchi pakoda stuffed with onions, tomato and chilli powder. I sprinkled some of the add on masala served alongside. They really enhanced the taste and flavour.

> Lemon coriander soup-
Diced veges simmered in veg broth. Consistency was thick and tastewise really good.

> Masala wada:
Deep fried wada made of chana dal and mix of spices. Wadas were sumptuous, fluffy and crunchy on oustside. Aftertaste was spicy. Highly recommended!

> Drumstick sambar-
Popular South Indian dish- cooked with toor dal, chopped onion and tomatoes. Drumsticks were properly cooked. Really delicious, flavorful and healthy sambar.

> Tomato rice-
Masala rice made with tomato, onion, dal and spices. It was slightly spicy but taste extremely good. Comfort food.

Overall this place can be visited for quality family fine dine experience. Definitely vising in near future to try their non veg food and other dishes.

A delivery kitchen with a dine in option, we tried Indizza Delivery Kitchen, Peddar Road.
Quaint, little outlet with an open kitchen for the customers to get an insight into the cooking, it was a lovely experience. 
We chose to order the Basil Mushroom Spinach and Cheese starter along with Chicken Achari Tikka. The mushrooms were heavenly and left us salivating for more! The chicken was spicy and a little salty due to the flavour combination of acchar but definitely succulent.

I have always been a big fan of Indizza - The Delivery Kitchen ever since it opened in Worli! Had ordered for food from there and was really impressed! Was excited to hear that they recently opened a delivery and takeaway outlet near Vama, Kemp's Corner Flyover, Pedder Road! And finally I decided to visit this new one.

First thought, I would do a takeaway, but there is space for about 6 to 8 people to sit and eat at the outlet. So thought might as well do that! This outlet delivers to places in the radius of 4 kms or so, which means pretty much entire of South Mumbai. Indizza serves North Indian food - Appetizers, Rolls, Curries, Dal, Rotis and Desserts! In short a wholesome meal. They have reasonable amount of Veg and Non Veg options which I believe would cater to all.

Talking about what all I tried at Indizza -

We started with few starters - Bharwaan Mushroom Tikka, Paneer Jeera Mirch Tikka and Aloo Achari Tikka. I would personally recommend these starters in the same order. Mushroom Tikka is too good, lipsmacking! In case one doesn't prefer mushroom, then one should go for Paneer Jeera Mirch Tikka, there are other options as well in Paneer Tikka. Paneer was soft and all appetizers came along with Pudina mint chutney and some onions. Aloo Achari lacked the taste though.

We ordered for some drinks. Besides the regular soft drinks they serve Nimbu Pani and Pudina Nimbu Pani! Nothing fancy about it and the drinks were also served in basic bottles, but effective and refreshing taste to go along with the food!

Next from the rolls section, we ordered the Paneer Makhani Roll, wrapped neatly in an aluminium silver foil. Rolls are served in tandoori or Roomali roti! We had this roll in Roomali Roti. Yummy, the filling was too good, roti cooked well. No complaints at all. Would recommend people trying rolls as per their likings and preferences.

Moving to the mains, we ordered for Dal Makhani, Paneer Tikka Masala. From the Rotis, I was really excited to try the Truffle Cheese Naan. Naan was cut in a way Pizza is cut. Stuffed with regular cheese flavoured with Truffle. Truffles have garlicky flavour and a peculiar aroma. I personally loved it, some may feel it to be pungent. So please use your discretion. For me Truffle Cheese Naan was the Highlight or Star of the evening! Dal Makhani creamy - rich - thick, perfect in taste. Paneer Tikka Masala adequately spiced and rich in flavour! What an awesome meal.

Finally turned to desserts, tried the Gooey Chocolate. Served in a basic container, but loved the chocolate crumbles and topping on fresh swedish chocolate cake! Divine and perfect way to end!

I am happy, that I decided to have my meal there rather than takeaway. Liked the overall experience, staff was courteous, Mr. Vijay was helpful! Would recommend all, do try Indizza, definitely worth every penny that you spend!

Curry was spicy and served hot.Tasted fabulous with garlic naan  and missi roti!! I liked garlic naan more ,it was yummy and lovely with that maratha curry!Highly Recommend this maratha Mutton curry

Yeda Republic in Juhu is undoubtedly one the quirkiest clubs in town. I've been a frequent visitor here and I've had one hell of a night every single time I've visited this place. They've come up with this new beautiful entrance which is decorated with golden fairy lights. They have a huge green wall opposite the entrance as its selfie point. Yeda Republic is an evil styled lounge bar with space suits and dark alleys. The lounge bar is located underground in the basement with Carribean flags with life like props wearing space suits, gas masks and respiratory pipes while you walk your way down. They have huge a jeep like structure located right in the centre where cute little staff members dressed up in spacesuits dance during weekends. Dark zones, Gas chambers, Ceiling with human bodies strapped with masks, ropes, jute bags, tunnel-like entry to the restrooms, waiters dressed like prisoners in orange one-piece suits are some of the traits of this lounge. The bar counter is clearly the highlight of this place with large cylindrical pipes which drop down from the ceiling and houses the Bar Bottles, for the rest of the display. They also have a fancy telephone booth with 5 ancient telephones. Talking about the food, the menu is a little compact when it comes to food. One thing they could work on is their menu. They have a wide bar menu but only 4 mocktails and 3 desserts in all. Also, I'd recommend y'all to place your order for maincourse and desserts along with the appetizers itself as they take a while to prepare the food.

We'd ordered :
In Mocktails :
1. Fruitshoot - Mixed fruits blended with sugar and vanilla ice-cream. The taste was good. If you like your drink sweet, you can opt for this one.

2. Lipstick - This is a tiny glass of mocktail having a very attractive red colour consisting of orange, mint, cranberry juice and peach crush.

In Cocktails :
1. Bloody Mary - This is our all time favorite, red colored spicy cocktail which will surely get you in the mood.

In Appetizers :
1. Cheese Corn Nuggets - Seven pieces of nuggets having melted cheese, corn and capsicum in its filling served with a dip. They are medium spicy in taste. 

2. Chicken Lollipop - Six pieces of chicken legs served with green chutney. They have a tangy taste. 

In Mains :
1. Chicken Sphaghetti Pasta with Pesto Sauce - They have three options in pasta base, ie. Sphaghetti, Macaroni and Penne Pasta. We'd opted for Sphaghetti Pasta in Pesto Sauce with chicken as its add on. It's served with two long garlic breads, garnished with cheese and black olives.

2. Chicken Makhani Pizza - This is a thin crust pizza which has Makhani sauce in its base topped with chicken pieces and cheese.

In Dessert :
1. Paan Falooda - I'm a huge paan lover so went for this one. This a satiating glass of falooda with paan syrup, jelly, almonds, cashews and french vanilla ice-cream.

A place with comfortable seating arrangements. More of white background. A place that serves varieties of cuisines. Chinese as well as Indian preferably North Indian cuisine, Mughlai dishes, and of course sea food too. 

I visited the place on Friday evening and it was all packed by 9 pm. More of a family restaurant. I saw many a families having dinner there. 

Generally I prefer to have non veg food but looking at a delicious menu here, I tried all vegetarian food and it was awesome. Appetizer as well as main course were delicious. 

Tried a few mocktails and they were worth every penny you would end up paying. 

Pinacolada: My usual drink. When in confusion, choose pinacolada. They had it perfectly. The blend was proportionate in a perfect way. Pineapple with coconut. Vanilla ice cream. 

Fruit punch: Mix of fruits. I requested them to make it without sugar syrup and they rightly did so. Refreshing. Fresh fruits. One of the best fruit punch preparations, I had in recent time. A bit tangy. 

The staff is very cooperative and helped me in deciding my orders. 

Tandoor broccoli and paneer: Generally, these two are different dishes: tandoor paneer and tandoor broccoli. I requested them to have it combined and they obliged it happily. Served with green chutney and red sauce. Perfectly grilled veggies. Delicious. Luscious paneer. Broccoli too was delicious. Paneer topped with cheese and coriander. Broccoli also topped with coriander. Onion slaw topped with mint and lemon. Broccoli had mustard feel as it was marinated with mustard sauce. Paneer was grilled along with onion, capsicum, and pineapple. 

Hara bhara kebab with galouti kebab: Melting kebabs. Galouti kebabs were better than hara bhara kebab but again this is sin comparing two food dishes, isn't it? Loved both the kebabs. Served with tomato sauce. Galouti kebab were made from beetroot. Filled with cheese and cream. 

In main course, we had tawa mushroom along with chura paratha. 

Tawa mushroom was cooked properly. Fresh mushroom. Gravy was perfectly fine. Goes well with chura paratha. Mushroom gravy had capsicum, bell peppers. Topped with coriander. Red gravy. Delicious. Paratha was something unique, it was more like warqi paratha. 

In dessert, we had gulab jamun rabdi. Delicious rabdi topped with gulab jamun. Perfectly sweetened rabdi. Loved the dessert too. Chilled rabdi served with hot gulab jamun. Topped with dry fruits. 

Overall, this is a nice place. The food is good. They have given emphasis on hygiene also. Cleanliness was upto the mark.

Who hasn't heard bout B Bhagat Tarachand?!! You will hardly find anyone!. It's famous since generations & widely spread across Mumbai!. We had been here recently again, situated@N.S. road, near Panch Rasta, Mulund West!.

The surrounding ambience has pleasing vibes & aroma is soothing too!. The decors are well lit & gives the feel of its long lavish legacy of generations!.

The staff here is very friendly & prompt while placing several orders & suggestions & serving hot too!.
Dharmendra, incharge for our table was very attentive to recommend & serve with delight!.

Let's checkout the food we had ordered here, 

Papad Churi was totally crunchy & tossed up with onion & chaat!. You just can't stop after one bite!.. It's all time regular favourites for most of the tables!. Surely try this dish for starters!.

We next ordered Chinese Platter, it was finger licking & platter had sufficient quantity for sharing wise!. Several Chinese items include manchurian balls, Vej crispy, paneer chilli & spring rolls & salad in sidings!.

We also had Paneer Tikka Dry, it was mouthwatering to glance & craving for more!. The spices were nicely blend & paneer was coated crisply & lip smacking!.

Paneer Cheese Tikka, is a nice fusion of seasoned paneer & over loaded cheese!. If you love both, surely go for this tikka, it's finger licking awesome!.

Bhagat Tarachand Special Thali  gives a glimpse of its succesful tradition it carries!. Balanced so well with ghee chapatis, 2 sabji of own choice, papad, dal, raita etc!. It's wholesome & flavourful by all means!.

Gulab Jamun is tender soft & sweet to its core, lingering sweetness for a long time to cherish!. Surely good to try Gulab Jamuns for dessert!.

Icecream slice looked tempting & every slice of it was yummm!! After heavy dining, it's truly a bliss to pounce on desserts like this for sweet tooth lovers!.

B Bhagat Tarachand is a proven excellence & you surely visit this place quite often to experience it's awesome treat & hospitality!. Thankyou!. ‚ù§
